              Here at C.A.Gs in Midland, Texas, Mark &amp; Teri Benjamin have hand-raised captive-bred Congo and Timneh African Greys since 2014 — and the question we field most is simply <em>which food do I buy?</em> This is our honest review of the best African Grey pellet brands, where seed mixes and treats actually belong, the foraging products worth owning, and how to switch a Grey to a new food without a fight.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 md:justify-start">
              <a href="#pellet-brands" class="font-sora rounded-full bg-clay px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition-colors hover:bg-clay-dk">Jump to the Pellet Brands →</a>
